# Refactor Rules

Use **@refactor** when refactoring a file or splitting code.

This rule references:

- **Refactor current file**: `@rules/refactor/file-refactor.mdc` — one symbol per file, no inline types/helpers; run check after
- **TypeScript refactoring**: `@rules/typescript/refactoring-typescript.mdc` — move types to `types/`, helpers to `utils/`; index.ts and barrels: see `@rules/core/code-quality-guidelines.mdc`

## Short summary

- One exported symbol per file; extract types to `types/`, helpers to `utils/`.
- `index.ts` is allowed **only** as a single public entrypoint for a vertical slice/feature (explicit named re-exports, no `export *`). Avoid generic barrel files.
- Mandatory: run project check script after refactor.
